x4freetext: -PROPERTIES OF LEVELS INDUCED BY 0 TO 30 KEV NEUTRONS
IN STABLE ISOTOPES OF TELLURIUM.-(IN FRENCH).
PHOTO-NEUTRONS FROM A NATURAL URANIUM TARGET
MODERATED BY A 2.9 CM THICK POLYETHYLENE SHEET.
.ENERGY GAPS IN PEAKS ARE DUE TO THE SAMPLE THICKNESS.
THE NATURAL SAMPLES WERE COOLED TO LIQUID
NITROGEN TEMPERATURE, 77 DEGREE K WITH A DEBYE
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 103.74 M.
.CROSS-SECTIONS IN PEAKS SHOW INFLUENCE FROM THE SAMPLE
